{
  "doc_id": "34655",
  "text": "Heat can also indirectly affect the amount of PAs per berry by impacting on the number of seeds per berry [CITATION_1] and/or the physiological development of seeds such as a delay in seed ripening [CITATION_2] . However, where evaluated, seed composition generally shows very little variation due to abiotic factors [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . This may be due to their protection by the first two berry pericarp layers which are skin and pulp, as well as the thick and hard seed coat. In addition, PA biosynthesis is independent from that of the rest of the berry and appears to be programmed early in berry development, which might explain why it is not affected by abiotic factors.",
